===2020===
The [[2020 United States census]] reported that Muir Beach had a population of 304. The population density was {{convert|616.6|PD/sqmi|PD/km2|sp=us|adj=off}}. The racial makeup of Muir Beach was 273 (89.8%) [[White Americans|White]], 5 (1.6%) [[African Americans|African American]], 1 (0.3%) [[Native Americans in the United States|Native American]], 10 (3.3%) [[Asian Americans|Asian]], 0 (0.0%) [[Pacific Islander Americans|Pacific Islander]], 3 (1.0%) from [[Race (United States Census)|other races]], and 12 (3.9%) from two or more races. [[Hispanic and Latino Americans|Hispanic or Latino]] of any race were 10 persons (3.3%).<ref name=DP1>{{cite web |title=Muir Beach CDP, California; DP1: Profile of General Population and Housing Characteristics - 2020 Census of Population and Housing |url=https://data.census.gov/table/DECENNIALDP2020.DP1?g=1600000US0649950 |website=US Census Bureau |access-date=May 30, 2025}}</ref>

The census reported that 299 people (98.4% of the population) lived in households, 5 (1.6%) lived in non-institutionalized group quarters, and no one was institutionalized.<ref name=DP1/>

There were 135 households, out of which 32 (23.7%) had children under the age of 18 living in them, 65 (48.1%) were married-couple households, 13 (9.6%) were [[cohabitation|cohabiting]] couple households, 25 (18.5%) had a female householder with no partner present, and 32 (23.7%) had a male householder with no partner present. 40 households (29.6%) were one person, and 19 (14.1%) were one person aged 65 or older. The average household size was 2.21.<ref name=DP1/> There were 81 [[family (U.S. Census)|families]] (60.0% of all households).<ref>{{cite web |title=Muir Beach CDP, California; P16: Household Type - 2020 Census of Population and Housing |url=https://data.census.gov/table/DECENNIALDHC2020.P16?g=1600000US0649950 |website=US Census Bureau |access-date=May 30, 2025}}</ref>

The age distribution was 45 people (14.8%) under the age of 18, 23 people (7.6%) aged 18 to 24, 54 people (17.8%) aged 25 to 44, 81 people (26.6%) aged 45 to 64, and 101 people (33.2%) who were 65{{nbsp}}years of age or older. The median age was 53.7{{nbsp}}years. For every 100 females, there were 108.2 males.<ref name=DP1/>

There were 160 housing units at an average density of {{convert|324.5|/mi2|/km2|disp=preunit|units&nbsp;|units|}}, of which 135 (84.4%) were occupied. Of these, 101 (74.8%) were owner-occupied, and 34 (25.2%) were occupied by renters.<ref name=DP1/>

===2010===
[[File:Muir Beach Waves.JPG|thumb|left| 300px|Waves on Muir Beach]]
At the [[2010 United States Census|2010 census]] Muir Beach had a population of 310. The population density was {{convert|629.0|PD/sqmi|PD/km2|sp=us|adj=off}}. The racial makeup of Muir Beach was 283 (91.3%) White, 5 (1.6%) African American, 1 (0.3%) Native American, 12 (3.9%) Asian, 1 (0.3%) from other races, and 8 (2.6%) from two or more races.  Hispanic or Latino of any race were 7 people (2.3%).<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.census.gov/2010census/popmap/ipmtext.php?fl=06:0649950|archive-url=https://archive.today/20140715031908/http://www.census.gov/2010census/popmap/ipmtext.php?fl=06:0649950|url-status=dead|archive-date=July 15, 2014|title=2010 Census Interactive Population Search: CA - Muir Beach CDP|publisher=U.S. Census Bureau|access-date=July 12, 2014}}</ref>

The census reported that 95.8% of the population lived in households and 4.2% lived in non-institutionalized group quarters.

There were 141 households, 27 (19.1%) had children under the age of 18 living in them, 79 (56.0%) were [[marriage|opposite-sex married couples]] living together, 4 (2.8%) had a female householder with no husband present, 3 (2.1%) had a male householder with no wife present.  There were 11 (7.8%) [[POSSLQ|unmarried opposite-sex partnerships]], and 1 (0.7%) [[same-sex partnerships|same-sex married couples or partnerships]]. 39 households (27.7%) were one person and 11 (7.8%) had someone living alone who was 65 or older. The average household size was 2.11.  There were 86 families (61.0% of households); the average family size was 2.47.

The age distribution was 38 people (12.3%) under the age of 18, 10 people (3.2%) aged 18 to 24, 56 people (18.1%) aged 25 to 44, 138 people (44.5%) aged 45 to 64, and 68 people (21.9%) who were 65 or older.  The median age was 52.6 years. For every 100 females, there were 102.6 males.  For every 100 females aged 18 and over, there were 106.1 males.

There were 162 housing units at an average density of {{convert|328.7|/sqmi|/km2|sp=us|adj=off}}, of which 73.8% were owner-occupied and 26.2% were occupied by renters. The homeowner vacancy rate was 1.0%; the rental vacancy rate was 2.6%. 75.2% of the population lived in owner-occupied housing units and 20.6% lived in rental housing units.

===2000===
At the [[2000 United States census|2000 census]], the median household income was $125,402 and the median family income  was $152,174. The per capita income for the CDP was $66,476.  None of the families and 10.5% of the population were living below the [[poverty line]].<ref>[http://factfinder.census.gov/servlet/SAFFFacts?_event=Search&geo_id=&_geoContext=&_street=&_county=muir+beach&_cityTown=muir+beach&_state=04000US06&_zip=&_lang=en&_sse=on&pctxt=fph&pgsl=010&show_2003_tab=&redirect=Y U.S. Census Bureau, Muir Beach CDP, California Fact Sheet] {{Webarchive|url=https://archive.today/20200212053624/http://factfinder.census.gov/servlet/SAFFFacts?_event=Search&geo_id=&_geoContext=&_street=&_county=muir+beach&_cityTown=muir+beach&_state=04000US06&_zip=&_lang=en&_sse=on&pctxt=fph&pgsl=010&show_2003_tab=&redirect=Y |date=February 12, 2020 }}, accessed June 12, 2007</ref>

